Ensure the correct use of HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.).
Ensure proper use of HTTP status codes (e.g., 200 for success, 404 for not found, 400 for bad requests, 500 for server errors).
Ensure the API provides meaningful error responses (e.g., JSON-formatted error messages) with appropriate status codes.
Validation for input data (e.g., required fields, formats like email or phone numbers).
Define how pagination works for endpoints that return lists of resources (e.g., use of page, size parameters).

